🧱 1. THE PLANT LAYOUT (Physical ↔ Logical Hybrid)

Think in zones, like a real refinery:

⸻

🚪 Zone A — Intake & Ingestion (The Gates)

Purpose: safely capture raw flow

Sources:
	•	Apps (your Preference Arena, tools, platforms)
	•	APIs (partners, public datasets)
	•	Events (clicks, decisions, time-to-choice)
	•	Context streams (time, device, environment)

Key systems:
	•	Stream ingestion (Kafka/PubSub style)
	•	Schema detection (auto + enforced)
	•	Identity resolution (pseudonymous IDs)

Pantheon mapping:
	•	Spider → intake routing
	•	Hound → anomaly detection at entry

⸻

🧼 Zone B — Cleaning & Normalization (The Wash)

Purpose: remove noise, align formats

Processes:
	•	Deduplication
	•	Missing value handling
	•	Format standardization
	•	Outlier flagging (not deleting—tagging)

Output:
	•	Clean, structured events

👉 This is where most pipelines stop. Yours is just getting started.

⸻

🧬 Zone C — Compression & Structuring (The Distillation Column)

Purpose: convert raw data into meaningful primitives

Core transforms:
	•	State + Δ + relation (your compression invariant)
	•	Event → decision → outcome chains
	•	Temporal sequencing
	•	Context binding

Example:

Raw: "User clicked button"
Becomes:
User preferred A > B under condition Z with hesitation 1.2s

Artifacts created:
	•	Decision objects
	•	Relationship graphs
	•	Temporal traces

Pantheon mapping:
	•	Raven → compression
	•	Mother Duck → ledgering

⸻

🧠 Zone D — Modeling & Pattern Extraction (The Reactor)

Purpose: generate insight and predictive power

Engines:
	•	Ranking systems (Elo / Bayesian)
	•	Clustering (taste vectors)
	•	Graph embeddings
	•	Sequence models (behavior prediction)

Outputs:
	•	Taste vectors (identity fingerprints)
	•	Preference gradients
	•	Prediction models
	•	Anomaly signatures

Pantheon mapping:
	•	Mirror → truth / validation
	•	Dragonfly → perspective transforms

⸻

📦 Zone E — Productization (The Packaging Line)

Purpose: turn insights into sellable, usable units

🔹 Signal Packages (your core product)

Types:
	•	Lead Signals → “Users likely to buy X”
	•	Taste Profiles → identity vectors
	•	Trend Signals → emerging patterns
	•	Decision APIs → “best option given context”

Each package includes:
	•	Context metadata
